Problem Statement 1

 The Agricultural industry is facing challenges with food wastage, Effects of climatic conditions and Environmental Issues that are affecting its profitability and sustainability. In May 2018 to April 2019 there was record breaking in the US with the wettest weather and fewest crops planted in recent history. There were fewer than 1/2 of projected  crops planted by mid-May in 2018 due to weather concerns. This is the lowest percentage at that point in the year since 1995. This not only decreased the harvest projected but it also affected the Profitability and sustainability of Agriculture.
